Watch live as cardinals choose the new pope. Candidates need a two-thirds majority, or 89 votes.

New pope greets world with calls for peace

Cardinal Robert Prevost has taken the name Leo XIV. He is the first American pope in the 2,000-year history of the Catholic Church.

More than half the world’s population sees AP journalism every day.
